%description:
TCP AccECN (Workstream G) G5.1: ACE field read side (mod-8 delta resolution,
deliveredCePkts). Both endpoints tcpEcnMode="accecn". The client sends
9000B (9 MSS-sized segments) in one window-sized burst; the tester marks
all 9 data segments CE and drops the server's first 8 individual ACKs, so
only the 9th (cumulative, ack=9001) survives -- the client sees a single
ACK covering all 9 newly-delivered "packets" (INET has no segment-boundary
tracking once bytes enter the byte-range-based send/rexmit-queue model, so
deliveredPktsThisAck approximates packets as ceil(newly-delivered-bytes /
mss), the same reduction Linux's own tcp_skb_pcount collapses to for a
non-GSO/TSO sender -- see the code comment).

The server's rcvCePkts reaches 9 (one per CE-marked segment), so its
surviving ACK encodes ace=(9+5)&0x7=6. The client's naive delta --
(receivedAce - 5 - deliveredCePkts_before) & 0x7 = (6-5-0)&7 = 1 -- and its
safeDelta candidate -- 9 - ((9-1)&7) = 9 -- disagree, because 9 packets were
delivered in one ACK (> 7) so the mod-8 counter is genuinely ambiguous: the
client cannot tell "1 CE mark" from "1 + one full wraparound = 9".

Linux (and now INET) resolve this ambiguity with the packets-acked EWMA
(pkts_acked_ewma / ACK_COMP_THRESH in __tcp_accecn_process). This is the
client's FIRST ACK, so the EWMA is seeded directly to deliveredPktsThisAck
(9 << 6 = 576), which exceeds the ACK_COMP_THRESH<<PREC = 4<<6 = 256 gate.
A high EWMA means large ACKs are the NORM for this flow (receiver-side ACK
compression / GRO), so a big single-ACK packet count is EXPECTED and does NOT
imply a counter wrap -- the naive delta (1), not safeDelta (9), is chosen.
resolvedDelta=1, deliveredCePkts=1. This deliberately trades exact CE
accounting for robustness against ACK compression, matching the real kernel
(verified: the corpus's tcp_accecn_delivered_largeack/largeack2/maxack/
2ndlargeack goldens require exactly this behavior).

safeDelta now wins only in the opposite regime -- a flow whose ACKs are
routinely SMALL (EWMA <= 256) that then takes a genuine wrap on one larger
ACK. This test exercises the high-EWMA (naive) branch; the trace line's
naiveDelta/safeDelta/resolvedDelta fields make which branch fired directly
observable. Asserted via an EV_INFO trace line (AccECN ACE decode: ...) added
to make deliveredCePkts observable in a module test, since it otherwise only
reaches an emitted signal (not recorded here, record-vector-results=false).

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script="a3 ce;a4 ce;a5 ce;a6 ce;a7 ce;a8 ce;a9 ce;a10 ce;a11 ce;b2 delete;b3 delete;b4 delete;b5 delete;b6 delete;b7 delete;b8 delete;b9 delete"

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=0.5s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=9000B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"
*.*_tcp.delayedAcksEnabled = false
*.*_tcp.initialWindow = "rfc6928"

*.*_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "accecn"

# tcp-legacy.ini sets advertisedWindow=7504; OMNeT++ ini resolution takes the FIRST matching
# entry, so this override -- needed so the full 9000B burst fits in one window and all 9
# segments go out without waiting on an intermediate ACK -- must appear BEFORE the include.
*.*_tcp.advertisedWindow = 20000

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Server's surviving (9th) ACK: ace=6=0b110 (cwr+ae, no ece), covering all 9 CE-marked segments.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.503 B010] A.1000 < B.2000: A W N ack 9001 win 20000
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# The ACE resolution: a first big ACK (EWMA seeded to 9<<6=576 > 256) is read as
%# ACK compression, so the naive delta (1) is chosen over safeDelta (9), matching
%# Linux's pkts_acked_ewma heuristic. G7's option-evidence refinement is inert here
%# (accEcnOptionEnabled unset, cebDeltaValid=0).
%contains: stdout
AccECN ACE decode: receivedAce=6 deliveredPktsThisAck=9 naiveDelta=1 safeDelta=9 cebDeltaValid=0 cebDelta=-1 resolvedDelta=1 deliveredCePkts=1
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
